sentences.content: The following exercises allow me to fill in the prompts given the corresponding response lists in increasingly more difficult ordering until no response list is shown.
He is going to the grocery [_store_].
The car has a full tank of [_gasoline_].
She bought a dress in the womens [_department_].
Do you have this in another [_size_]?
The farmers market has very fresh [_vegetables_].
I tried it on in a fitting [_room_].
Push the cart up and down the [_aisle_].
You find the steak in the meat [_section_].
She buys fresh bread at the [_bakery_].
You can find cheap deals at Dollar [_Tree_].
He looked for athletic shoes at [_Nike_].
